The data is related with direct marketing campaigns of a Portuguese banking institution. The marketing campaigns were based on phone calls. Often, more than one contact to the same client was required, in order to access if the product (bank term deposit) would be (or not) subscribed.¶

Input variables:

bank client data:¶

1 - age (numeric) 2 - job : type of job (categorical: "admin.","unknown","unemployed","management","housemaid","entrepreneur","student", "blue-collar","self-employed","retired","technician","services") 3 - marital : marital status (categorical: "married","divorced","single"; note: "divorced" means divorced or widowed) 4 - education (categorical: "unknown","secondary","primary","tertiary") 5 - default: has credit in default? (binary: "yes","no") 6 - balance: average yearly balance, in euros (numeric) 7 - housing: has housing loan? (binary: "yes","no") 8 - loan: has personal loan? (binary: "yes","no")

related with the last contact of the current campaign:¶

9 - contact: contact communication type (categorical: "unknown","telephone","cellular") 10 - day: last contact day of the month (numeric) 11 - month: last contact month of year (categorical: "jan", "feb", "mar", ..., "nov", "dec") 12 - duration: last contact duration, in seconds (numeric)

other attributes:¶

13 - campaign: number of contacts performed during this campaign and for this client (numeric, includes last contact) 14 - pdays: number of days that passed by after the client was last contacted from a previous campaign (numeric, -1 means client was not previously contacted) 15 - previous: number of contacts performed before this campaign and for this client (numeric) 16 - poutcome: outcome of the previous marketing campaign (categorical: "unknown","other","failure","success")

Output variable (desired target): 17 - Target - has the client subscribed a term deposit? (binary: "yes","no")

Create a method to evaluate the Model, as we may have to do it for multiple models¶

In [145]:
def evaluateModel(model,name):
    print("######Evaluate the model %s ###########"%(name))
    print("Training Accuracy score : \t %s "%(model.score(x_train,y_train)))
    print("Test Accuracy score : \t %s "%(model.score(x_test,y_test)))
    print("Confusion matrix \n\t %s"%(metrics.confusion_matrix(y_test,y_pred)))
    print("classicification report \n %s"%(metrics.classification_report(y_test,y_pred)))

Observation of Result¶

  • Used decision tree(DT) without any hyper parameters , DT will infact overfit here
  • As we can see fromt he accuracy score , training score is 100% where as it has not done very good performance when run on test data, which has given 87% accuracy
  • Also from looking at the cofusion metrx, precision and recall from classification report, we can see that model has done good prediction in identifying target 0 (93%) where as done very poor in predicting target 1 (%45)
  • so this model is not a right choice for production deployment

Now Lets perform some Data Cleaning and then re create the model & evalute¶

  • From our previous analysis as part of EDA we found out that few of the features data may negatively impact in model building, we will remove them from our analysis

  • Copying previous Analysis here

    From value counts¶

    • job, we see 0.6% of data we dont have the job type, it can be removed from our anlaysis
    • education, is unknown for 4% of the data, even this we can remove
    • default, less than 2% data is available for credit defaulter yes, also from the box plot we see that non of these customer subscribed for TD, so it will not be of much use for our analysis, we can delete these 2% data
    • contant, around 6% of data is there for telephone , this may not be of much helpfull, we can remove this data too
    • poutcome, we see that 3% of customer did subscribe after previous marketing. 81% of customers were not contacted or have no data about them.

    from the bar plot¶

    • job , we can see that majority of the customer job type is blue-collar, management and technician. subscription for term deposite is more too from these job types customer. Also we see customer with job type retired and admin too have more subscription toward TD . There are some customers whose job type is unknown we can later think of removing these
    • marital, we see more records for married and single and also notice that married customers subscription to TD is more compared to single and divorced
    • education, we see that secondary and tertiary customer count is more in number also they have subscribed to TD more that other education type
    • default, we see that those who have credit default have not at all subscribed to TD
    • housing, we notice that those who have no housing loan have subscribed to TD more than those who have housing loan
    • loan, this is similar to housing loan. ppl with personal loan have not subscribed much to TD
    • month, we see that more number of customer contacted in the month of aug, jul and may, also we see more subscirption happened on same months

    From the box/violine plot we can infer¶

    • age, most of values fall roughly between 27 to 60 , and has few outliers too
    • balance , density of it is moslty between -10000 to 20000 however we see values are widely spread to extreem values close to 100000
    • duration, most of the value fall between 0 to 1500 , however data is spread to 5000 seconds too which can be considered as outliers
    • campaign , number of contacts performed during this campaign, most of the values fall between 0 to 10 however values spread widely till 60 , again outliers
    • We also see that pdays has outliers too , however its measure of time/interval, may have to check if it needs to be taken care by using impute methods
    • previous , number of contacts performed before this campaign , looks it has lot of outliers or may be these are invalid values(extreem values)

Summary¶

  • As part of EDA univariate/multivariate we found out below

    we noticed that most of the feature set had descrete set of values also noticed that few of the featues like age, balance, previous had outliers , few had unknown values as part of histogram plot we found out that most of the features were not symetric and were skewed with box/violin plot we noticed most of the data for all the features was falling withing the IQR however some of the features had outliers infact they seemed like invalid values with bar plot we found that few features had unknown values as majority types , also found out that what all category values have positive/negative impact on target values then with value counts we confirmed our observatoin of bar plot and decided to drop out data of few features like removing unknow type from job, education feature set, also droping poutcome

  • Model building - part1

    we created multiple models like DT, DT with regularization, then used ensemble methods Bagging and Boosting of all these models we found out that Ensemble Methods - GradientBoost gave us good result with overall test score of 90%

  • Data cleaning

    we then proceeded with cleaning our data as identified earlier to check if that makes any difference in building best model we removed all the rows with unknown values for contact, default and job features Also droped poutcome feature

  • Model building - part2

    after cleanup we again ran the same models on new data set we notice that there was no improvment in the models however here also we found out that Ensemble Methods - GradientBoost performed best among all others

  • Final statement

    Though we applied multiple algorithm to build best model , we could not find any model that would give us 95% accurate even after data cleanup, we may try tuning the hyper parameters to find hte best results. However the best model we could build is using Ensemble Methods - GradientBoost which gave us 90% accuracy ( 93% in classifying target 0 and 65% in classiyiing target 1)
